node.text: Ten of my favourite images from our recent exploration of film. Shot on @kodak #Portra400 on 3 different cameras over the last few months. I‚Äôve gained so much from switching to film recently, it‚Äôs demanding of your attention, no time (or money!) for throwaway shots. Digital allows you to have thousands of great photos, convenient when you need to work fast. Film asks you to be far more in the moment, pay more attention to the light, you shoot only when it‚Äôs worth it. Just a different way of working as a photographer, but certainly I‚Äôll be making more time in the future to explore the world of film! ‚ö°Ô∏è thank you @ellagracedenton for always getting creative with me ‚ô•Ô∏è

Happy 1st December homies! This image of me in Scotland shot by @harry.travel reminded me of how much I enjoy being out in savage weather, the wilder the elements the more I feel feel alive, so long as I‚Äôve got a good jacket and waterproof shoes I‚Äôm all good üòÅ can‚Äôt wait to get my house in order so I can get back out into the wild shooting and enjoying my work. Dear @jeremyloops, congratulations on releasing your 2nd album ‚ÄòCritical As Water‚Äô out into the world üåç Three years ago I tracked you down, having resonated a lot with your 1st album and I‚Äôm so happy I followed my heart & the good vibes. Nothing has been the same since! The music you create is a beautiful and full representation of your power, grace & love. From day one I only ever wanted more people to hear and feel your music and your realness, in the hope it would inspire and empower others the way it continues to do so for me. Fast forward thee years, we‚Äôve lived together, travelled together around the world together and shared many incredible experiences. We both continue to navigate our crazy career choices and life missions, whilst always supporting each other‚Äôs dreams and always with the best intentions for those around us. You‚Äôre a messy fucker to live with, and one day you WILL miss a flight, but I hope you know that for me nothing beats getting lost in ideas and new songs at 3am with you after a whisky or three, whilst also trying to figure out this thing called life. Your new album is straight from the heart, I‚Äôve been shedding tears and layers to ‚ÄòVultures‚Äô all day. I can‚Äôt wait to go on tour with you üôèüèº much love brother, this is just the beginning ‚ù§Ô∏è p.s thanks for giving me the chance to shoot my first ever album and single covers üì∏üòåüåä

node.text: Myself & @diaryofalex had been swimming/shooting for about 45mins in the 12¬∞C Atlantic, my legs were cramped up & energy was low. Overconfidence pushed me to sit on the inside to capture this image, it was the first and smallest wave of the five wave set, about 5 seconds later the other four larger waves pushed me up the beach right near the rocks. Being washing machined by powerful waves is humbling, but being low on breaths and trying not to panic is when life gets real. Cramps were hindering my swimming ability, turbulent rip tides draining my oxygen and my mind cleared pretty quickly when I realised I went into survival mode, it happened quickly and I feel stronger for the experience. I ended up washed up on the beach with a camera full of images üëåüèº üåä

It's now available to watch online on BBC Three on iPlayer in the UK (we're working on getting it to the rest of the world shortly!) I'm incredibly proud of our first digital series, hopefully we'll get commissioned for more seasons.

node.text: My last image from the Scotland wildlife mission. Certainly a highlight of the year so far, and a nice reminder of how beautiful the British Isles are üôåüèº onto Dubai next ‚úàÔ∏è

Such beautiful conditions to see dolphins in Scotland, I love how oily the water looks in the image, shooting from a boat into he sun on a perfect afternoon making me feel very grateful for these experience. I hope the images do these animals justice üê¨

I think this is my best eagle shot from Scotland. The whitetail eagle is about to grab the fish from the water with talons the size of your fingers! Despite their 2.5m wingspan they are tricky to get in focus! üòå
üê¨ trying not to post 5 wildlife images a day right now, Scotland was a very successful Instagram mission!
Seeing dolphins in Scotland was a beautiful surprise, but seeing them breach was unforgettable üê¨ this is the only environment these creature should be viewed in üôåüèº #scotspirit
Scotland, where have you been all my life?! üòç a beautiful end to a day on the ocean sighting dolphins, swimming with seals & photographing it all üëåüèº #scotspirit
Puffins are my new favourite bird, we were hanging out with them on a cliff top for an hour and they were so friendly üòå I'm really enjoying these wildlife challenges! #ScotSpirit

We spent a full day on a boat in Scotland with a single goal of capturing Whitetail Eagles. It was one of the most challenging shoots I've ever embarked on, but we came away with strong images & invaluable shooting experience. This female scooped the fish right out of the water about 10m from our boat üôåüèº I've got many more images to share form this day! #scotspirit

node.text: One of the most memorable days of my life üôåüèº watch the vlog to see myself and @sliceofmatt tag along with the Anti Rhino Poaching unit as they team up with vets to save to a rhino shot by poachers. Photo by Ravi Gajjar #UniteAgainstPoaching

üêò Face to face with mother & baby elephant, my favourite animal in the Kruger National Park. We were mock charged by an elephant whilst walking near our open campsite, luckily the rangers managed to keep him at bay by shouting & walking towards the elephant! It's all in tomorrow's video...

Happy Earth Day! Hippos in the Crocodile River, Kruger Park.  I had the pleasure of observing the Honorary Rangers & the Anti Rhino Poaching Unit in @KrugerNationalPark. We tracked a rhino that had been shot poachers through the top of its back. The vets darted the rhino, cleaned the wounds, took DNA samples & tagged it. That, and many other rhino will survive thanks to the incredible commitment from the rangers on the ground. Needless to say I'm really stoked to work with these organisations & I hope to get more involved in the future. Full video will be live on my YouTube channel, link in bio üáøüá¶ üåç ‚ù§Ô∏è

Everyone, meet Gary! üòä He is a Common slugeater (Duberria lutrix) they are shy, slow-moving, inoffensive creatures that never attempt to bite, even when captured. They are also called ‚ÄòTabakrolletjies‚Äô in Afrikaans because of their habit of rolling up into a tight spiral with its head hidden in its coils when feeling threatened. Another shot from last Friday in Cape Town. I'd just spent a solid 5 mins trying to swim out through the hectic beach break, not easy with a big camera, then Jayden comes sliding along catching some shade. I was finally in the right place, and it was still only chest deep water! When you get caught inside here you dive to the sand and hold on, as the wave goes over the sudden change in water pressure plays havoc with your sinuses. Sunburnt, leg cramps, beat up, stinging eyes and I didn't even surf?! So worth it for images like this! I'll surf next time üòè
